Following the ongoing strike by the primary school teachers of the Local Education Authority (LEA) in Kuje Area Council of the FCT, the Chairman of the council, Abdullahi Suleiman Sabo, has inaugurated an 11-member committee to conduct a screening of the teachers. Sabo, while inaugurating the committee on Tuesday, said it was made up of the councilâ€™s Chief of Staff (CoS), Abdullahi Suleiman Sabo, as chairman, and the head of administration as secretary, noting that the composition of membership cut across various organisations which included UBEB and NUT. Chairman of the committee, Sabo, assured that they would carry out the assignment diligently. 